---
<article class="border rounded-lg p-6 bg-white shadow-sm">
  <header class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-4">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">GlyphMate 1.0.2</h3>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-medium rounded-full bg-teal-100 text-teal-800 px-2.5 py-0.5">Patch</span>
    </div>
    <time datetime="2025-10-05" class="text-sm text-gray-500">2025-10-05</time>
  </header>

  <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
    <div>
      <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Added</h4>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Security:</strong> Implemented a secure backend proxy using Firebase Cloud Functions to protect the Google Fonts API key.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Removed</h4>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1">
        <li>Removed the `.env` file and `flutter_dotenv` package from the client application; API keys are now stored securely on the backend proxy.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Fixed</h4>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1">
        <li>Resolved a networking issue where Windows release builds could not access the internet to fetch Google Fonts.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
